FBIS4-37765 "drnes122_k_94013" FBIS-NES-94-122 Daily Report 21 Jun 1994 IRAQ Saddam Orders 300-Percent Pay Bonus for Brain Surgeons Saddam Orders 300-Percent Pay Bonus for Brain Surgeons JN2106130494 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in Arabic 1030 GMT 21 Jun 94 JN2106130494 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network Arabic BFN [Text] Leader President Saddam Husayn has ordered that brain and nervous system surgeons be granted monthly allowances equal to 300 percent of their total monthly salaries. This has been announced to the Iraqi News Agency by Health Minister Dr. Umid Midhat Mubarak. He said the leader president has also ordered that brain and nervous system surgical operations conducted at the Health Ministry's hospitals be excluded from the current charge rates. He added that this generous gesture by leader President Saddam Husayn reflects appreciation and support for this scientific specialization, which requires meticulous precision and extreme and distinguished care for brain and nervous system patients. He said that this generous gesture will encourage this specialization, which is an important lifesaving specializations.
